223 void setFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) { 0
224 if (!(getSTI().hasFeature(Feature))) { 0
225 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI(); 0
226 setAvailableFeatures( 0
227 ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.ToggleFeature(FeatureString))); 0
228 } ----
229 } 0
230 ----
231 void clearFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) { 0
232 if (getSTI().hasFeature(Feature)) { 0
233 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI(); 0
234 setAvailableFeatures( 0
235 ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.ToggleFeature(FeatureString))); 0
236 } ----
237 } 0
238 ----
239 void pushFeatureBits() { 0
240 assert(FeatureBitStack.size() == ParserOptionsStack.size() && 0
241 "These two stacks must be kept synchronized"); ----
242 FeatureBitStack.push_back(getSTI().getFeatureBits()); 0
243 ParserOptionsStack.push_back(ParserOptions); 0
244 } 0
245 ----
246 bool popFeatureBits() { 0
247 assert(FeatureBitStack.size() == ParserOptionsStack.size() && 0
248 "These two stacks must be kept synchronized"); ----
249 if (FeatureBitStack.empty()) 0
250 return true; 0
251 ----
252 FeatureBitset FeatureBits = FeatureBitStack.pop_back_val(); 0
253 copySTI().setFeatureBits(FeatureBits); 0
254 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(FeatureBits)); 0
255 ----
256 ParserOptions = ParserOptionsStack.pop_back_val(); 0
257 ----
258 return false; 0
259 } ----

277 RISCVAsmParser(const MCSubtargetInfo &STI, MCAsmParser &Parser, 0
278 const MCInstrInfo &MII, const MCTargetOptions &Options) ----
279 : MCTargetAsmParser(Options, STI, MII) { 0
280 MCAsmParserExtension::Initialize(Parser); 0
281 ----
282 Parser.addAliasForDirective(".half", ".2byte"); 0
283 Parser.addAliasForDirective(".hword", ".2byte"); 0
284 Parser.addAliasForDirective(".word", ".4byte"); 0
285 Parser.addAliasForDirective(".dword", ".8byte"); 0
286 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits())); 0
287 ----
288 auto ABIName = StringRef(Options.ABIName); 0
289 if (ABIName.endswith("f") && !getSTI().hasFeature(RISCV::FeatureStdExtF)) { 0
290 errs() << "Hard-float 'f' ABI can't be used for a target that " 0
291 "doesn't support the F instruction set extension (ignoring " ----
292 "target-abi)\n"; 0
293 } else if (ABIName.endswith("d") && 0
294 !getSTI().hasFeature(RISCV::FeatureStdExtD)) { 0
295 errs() << "Hard-float 'd' ABI can't be used for a target that " 0
296 "doesn't support the D instruction set extension (ignoring " ----
297 "target-abi)\n"; 0
298 } ----
299 ----
300 // Use computeTargetABI to check if ABIName is valid. If invalid, output ----
301 // error message. ----
302 RISCVABI::computeTargetABI(STI.getTargetTriple(), STI.getFeatureBits(), 0
303 ABIName); ----
304 ----
305 const MCObjectFileInfo *MOFI = Parser.getContext().getObjectFileInfo(); 0
306 ParserOptions.IsPicEnabled = MOFI->isPositionIndependent(); 0
307 ----
308 if (AddBuildAttributes) 0
309 getTargetStreamer().emitTargetAttributes(STI, /*EmitStackAlign*/ false); 0
310 } 0

389 RISCVOperand(const RISCVOperand &o) : MCParsedAsmOperand() { ----
390 Kind = o.Kind; ----
391 StartLoc = o.StartLoc; ----
392 EndLoc = o.EndLoc; ----
393 switch (Kind) { ----
394 case KindTy::Register: ----
395 Reg = o.Reg; ----
396 break; ----
397 case KindTy::Immediate: ----
398 Imm = o.Imm; ----
399 break; ----
400 case KindTy::FPImmediate: ----
401 FPImm = o.FPImm; ----
402 break; ----
403 case KindTy::Token: ----
404 Tok = o.Tok; ----
405 break; ----
406 case KindTy::SystemRegister: ----
407 SysReg = o.SysReg; ----
408 break; ----
409 case KindTy::VType: ----
410 VType = o.VType; ----
411 break; ----
412 case KindTy::FRM: ----
413 FRM = o.FRM; ----
414 break; ----
415 case KindTy::Fence: ----
416 Fence = o.Fence; ----
417 break; ----
418 case KindTy::Rlist: ----
419 Rlist = o.Rlist; ----
420 break; ----
421 case KindTy::Spimm: ----
422 Spimm = o.Spimm; ----
423 break; ----
424 } ----
425 } ----

462 static bool evaluateConstantImm(const MCExpr *Expr, int64_t &Imm, 0
463 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind &VK) { ----
464 if (auto *RE = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
465 VK = RE->getKind(); 0
466 return RE->evaluateAsConstant(Imm); 0
467 } ----
468 ----
469 if (auto CE = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
470 VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
471 Imm = CE->getValue(); 0
472 return true; 0
473 } ----
474 ----
475 return false; 0
476 } ----

478 // True if operand is a symbol with no modifiers, or a constant with no ----
479 // modifiers and isShiftedInt(Op). ----
480 template bool isBareSimmNLsb0() const { 0
481 int64_t Imm; ----
482 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
483 if (!isImm()) 0
484 return false; 0
485 bool IsConstantImm = evaluateConstantImm(getImm(), Imm, VK); 0
486 bool IsValid; ----
487 if (!IsConstantImm) 0
488 IsValid = RISCVAsmParser::classifySymbolRef(getImm(), VK); 0
489 else ----
490 IsValid = isShiftedInt(Imm); 0
491 return IsValid && VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
492 } ----

494 // Predicate methods for AsmOperands defined in RISCVInstrInfo.td ----
495 ----
496 bool isBareSymbol() const { 0
497 int64_t Imm; ----
498 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
499 // Must be of 'immediate' type but not a constant. ----
500 if (!isImm() || evaluateConstantImm(getImm(), Imm, VK)) 0
501 return false; 0
502 return RISCVAsmParser::classifySymbolRef(getImm(), VK) && 0
503 VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
504 } ----
505 ----
506 bool isCallSymbol() const { 0
507 int64_t Imm; ----
508 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
509 // Must be of 'immediate' type but not a constant. ----
510 if (!isImm() || evaluateConstantImm(getImm(), Imm, VK)) 0
511 return false; 0
512 return RISCVAsmParser::classifySymbolRef(getImm(), VK) && 0
513 (VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_CALL || 0
514 VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_CALL_PLT); 0
515 } ----

569 /// Return true if the operand is a valid fli.s floating-point immediate. ----
570 bool isLoadFPImm() const { 0
571 if (isImm()) 0
572 return isUImm5(); 0
573 if (Kind != KindTy::FPImmediate) 0
574 return false; 0
575 int Idx = RISCVLoadFPImm::getLoadFPImm( 0
576 APFloat(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APInt(64, getFPConst()))); 0
577 // Don't allow decimal version of the minimum value. It is a different value ----
578 // for each supported data type. ----
579 return Idx >= 0 && Idx != 1; 0
580 } ----
581 ----
582 bool isImmXLenLI() const { 0
583 int64_t Imm; ----
584 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
585 if (!isImm()) 0
586 return false; 0
587 bool IsConstantImm = evaluateConstantImm(getImm(), Imm, VK); 0
588 if (VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_LO || VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_PCREL_LO) 0
589 return true; 0
590 // Given only Imm, ensuring that the actually specified constant is either ----
591 // a signed or unsigned 64-bit number is unfortunately impossible. ----
592 if (IsConstantImm) { 0
593 return VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None && 0
594 (isRV64Imm() || (isInt<32>(Imm) || isUInt<32>(Imm))); 0
595 } ----

597 return RISCVAsmParser::isSymbolDiff(getImm()); 0
598 } ----
599 ----
600 bool isImmXLenLI_Restricted() const { 0
601 int64_t Imm; ----
602 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
603 if (!isImm()) 0
604 return false; 0
605 bool IsConstantImm = evaluateConstantImm(getImm(), Imm, VK); 0
606 // 'la imm' supports constant immediates only. ----
607 return IsConstantImm && (VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None) && 0
608 (isRV64Imm() || (isInt<32>(Imm) || isUInt<32>(Imm))); 0
609 } ----

618 return false; 0

818 // If this a RV32 and the immediate is a uimm32, sign extend it to 32 bits. ----
819 // This allows writing 'addi a0, a0, 0xffffffff'. ----
820 static int64_t fixImmediateForRV32(int64_t Imm, bool IsRV64Imm) { 0
821 if (IsRV64Imm || !isUInt<32>(Imm)) 0
822 return Imm; 0
823 return SignExtend64<32>(Imm); 0
824 } ----

826 bool isSImm12() const { 0
827 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
828 int64_t Imm; ----
829 bool IsValid; ----
830 if (!isImm()) 0
831 return false; 0
832 bool IsConstantImm = evaluateConstantImm(getImm(), Imm, VK); 0
833 if (!IsConstantImm) 0
834 IsValid = RISCVAsmParser::classifySymbolRef(getImm(), VK); 0
835 else ----
836 IsValid = isInt<12>(fixImmediateForRV32(Imm, isRV64Imm())); 0
837 return IsValid && ((IsConstantImm && VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None) || 0
838 VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_LO || 0
839 VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_PCREL_LO || 0
840 VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_TPREL_LO); 0
841 } ----

978 ----
979 void print(raw_ostream &OS) const override { 0
980 auto RegName = [](MCRegister Reg) { 0
981 if (Reg) 0
982 return RISCVInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
983 else ----
984 return "noreg"; 0
985 }; ----
986 ----
987 switch (Kind) { 0
988 case KindTy::Immediate: 0
989 OS << *getImm(); 0
990 break; 0
991 case KindTy::FPImmediate: 0
992 break; 0
993 case KindTy::Register: 0
994 OS << ""; 0
995 break; 0
996 case KindTy::Token: 0
997 OS << "'" << getToken() << "'"; 0
998 break; 0
999 case KindTy::SystemRegister: 0
1000 OS << "'; 0
1001 break; 0
1002 case KindTy::VType: 0
1003 OS << " 0
1004 RISCVVType::printVType(getVType(), OS); 0
1005 OS << '>'; 0
1006 break; 0
1007 case KindTy::FRM: 0
1008 OS << " 0
1009 roundingModeToString(getFRM()); 0
1010 OS << '>'; 0
1011 break; 0
1012 case KindTy::Fence: 0
1013 OS << " 0
1014 OS << getFence(); 0
1015 OS << '>'; 0
1016 break; 0
1017 case KindTy::Rlist: 0
1018 OS << " 0
1019 RISCVZC::printRlist(Rlist.Val, OS); 0
1020 OS << '>'; 0
1021 break; 0
1022 case KindTy::Spimm: 0
1023 OS << " 0
1024 RISCVZC::printSpimm(Spimm.Val, OS); 0
1025 OS << '>'; 0
1026 break; 0
1027 } ----
1028 } 0

1117 static void addExpr(MCInst &Inst, const MCExpr *Expr, bool IsRV64Imm) { 0
1118 assert(Expr && "Expr shouldn't be null!"); 0
1119 int64_t Imm = 0; 0
1120 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
1121 bool IsConstant = evaluateConstantImm(Expr, Imm, VK); 0
1122 ----
1123 if (IsConstant) 0
1124 Inst.addOperand( 0
1125 MCOperand::createImm(fixImmediateForRV32(Imm, IsRV64Imm))); ----
1126 else ----
1127 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr)); 0
1128 } 0
1129 ----
1130 // Used by the TableGen Code ----
1131 void addRegOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1132 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1133 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(getReg())); 0
1134 } 0
1135 ----
1136 void addImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1137 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1138 addExpr(Inst, getImm(), isRV64Imm()); 0
1139 } 0
1140 ----
1141 void addFPImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1142 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1143 if (isImm()) { 0
1144 addExpr(Inst, getImm(), isRV64Imm()); 0
1145 return; 0
1146 } ----
1147 ----
1148 int Imm = RISCVLoadFPImm::getLoadFPImm( 0
1149 APFloat(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APInt(64, getFPConst()))); 0
1150 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm)); 0
1151 } ----
1152 ----
1153 void addFenceArgOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1154 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1155 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Fence.Val)); 0
1156 } 0
1157 ----
1158 void addCSRSystemRegisterOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1159 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1160 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(SysReg.Encoding)); 0
1161 } 0
1162 ----
1163 // Support non-canonical syntax: ----
1164 // "vsetivli rd, uimm, 0xabc" or "vsetvli rd, rs1, 0xabc" ----
1165 // "vsetivli rd, uimm, (0xc << N)" or "vsetvli rd, rs1, (0xc << N)" ----
1166 void addVTypeIOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1167 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1168 int64_t Imm = 0; 0
1169 if (Kind == KindTy::Immediate) { 0
1170 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
1171 bool IsConstantImm = evaluateConstantImm(getImm(), Imm, VK); 0
1172 (void)IsConstantImm; ----
1173 assert(IsConstantImm && "Invalid VTypeI Operand!"); 0
1174 } else { ----
1175 Imm = getVType(); 0
1176 } ----
1177 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm)); 0
1178 } 0
1179 ----
1180 void addRlistOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1181 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1182 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Rlist.Val)); 0
1183 } 0
1184 ----
1185 void addSpimmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1186 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1187 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Spimm.Val)); 0
1188 } 0
1189 ----
1190 void addFRMArgOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const { 0
1191 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!"); 0
1192 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(getFRM())); 0
1193 } 0
1194 }; ----
1195 } // end anonymous namespace. ----

1203 static MCRegister convertFPR64ToFPR16(MCRegister Reg) { 0
1204 assert(Reg >= RISCV::F0_D && Reg <= RISCV::F31_D && "Invalid register"); 0
1205 return Reg - RISCV::F0_D + RISCV::F0_H; 0
1206 } ----
1207 ----
1208 static MCRegister convertFPR64ToFPR32(MCRegister Reg) { 0
1209 assert(Reg >= RISCV::F0_D && Reg <= RISCV::F31_D && "Invalid register"); 0
1210 return Reg - RISCV::F0_D + RISCV::F0_F; 0
1211 } ----
1212 ----
1213 static MCRegister convertVRToVRMx(const MCRegisterInfo &RI, MCRegister Reg, 0
1214 unsigned Kind) { ----
1215 unsigned RegClassID; ----
1216 if (Kind == MCK_VRM2) 0
1217 RegClassID = RISCV::VRM2RegClassID; 0
1218 else if (Kind == MCK_VRM4) 0
1219 RegClassID = RISCV::VRM4RegClassID; 0
1220 else if (Kind == MCK_VRM8) 0
1221 RegClassID = RISCV::VRM8RegClassID; 0
1222 else ----
1223 return 0; 0
1224 return RI.getMatchingSuperReg(Reg, RISCV::sub_vrm1_0, 0
1225 &RISCVMCRegisterClasses[RegClassID]); 0
1226 } ----
1227 ----
1228 unsigned RISCVAsmParser::validateTargetOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &AsmOp, 0
1229 unsigned Kind) { ----
1230 RISCVOperand &Op = static_cast(AsmOp); 0
1231 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
1232 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1233 ----
1234 MCRegister Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
1235 bool IsRegFPR64 = ----
1236 RISCVMCRegisterClasses[RISCV::FPR64RegClassID].contains(Reg); 0
1237 bool IsRegFPR64C = ----
1238 RISCVMCRegisterClasses[RISCV::FPR64CRegClassID].contains(Reg); 0
1239 bool IsRegVR = RISCVMCRegisterClasses[RISCV::VRRegClassID].contains(Reg); 0
1240 ----
1241 // As the parser couldn't differentiate an FPR32 from an FPR64, coerce the ----
1242 // register from FPR64 to FPR32 or FPR64C to FPR32C if necessary. ----
1243 if ((IsRegFPR64 && Kind == MCK_FPR32) || 0
1244 (IsRegFPR64C && Kind == MCK_FPR32C)) { 0
1245 Op.Reg.RegNum = convertFPR64ToFPR32(Reg); 0
1246 return Match_Success; 0
1247 } ----
1248 // As the parser couldn't differentiate an FPR16 from an FPR64, coerce the ----
1249 // register from FPR64 to FPR16 if necessary. ----
1250 if (IsRegFPR64 && Kind == MCK_FPR16) { 0
1251 Op.Reg.RegNum = convertFPR64ToFPR16(Reg); 0
1252 return Match_Success; 0
1253 } ----
1254 // As the parser couldn't differentiate an VRM2/VRM4/VRM8 from an VR, coerce ----
1255 // the register from VR to VRM2/VRM4/VRM8 if necessary. ----
1256 if (IsRegVR && (Kind == MCK_VRM2 || Kind == MCK_VRM4 || Kind == MCK_VRM8)) { 0
1257 Op.Reg.RegNum = convertVRToVRMx(*getContext().getRegisterInfo(), Reg, Kind); 0
1258 if (Op.Reg.RegNum == 0) 0
1259 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1260 return Match_Success; 0
1261 } ----
1262 return Match_InvalidOperand; 0
1263 } ----
1264 ----
1265 unsigned RISCVAsmParser::checkTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst) { 0
1266 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode()); 0
1267 ----
1268 for (unsigned I = 0; I < MCID.NumOperands; ++I) { 0
1269 if (MCID.operands()[I].RegClass == RISCV::GPRPF64RegClassID) { 0
1270 const auto &Op = Inst.getOperand(I); 0
1271 assert(Op.isReg()); 0
1272 ----
1273 MCRegister Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
1274 if (((Reg.id() - RISCV::X0) & 1) != 0) 0
1275 return Match_RequiresEvenGPRs; 0
1276 } ----
1277 } ----
1278 ----
1279 return Match_Success; 0
1280 } ----

1282 bool RISCVAsmParser::generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1283 SMLoc ErrorLoc, int64_t Lower, int64_t Upper, ----
1284 const Twine &Msg = "immediate must be an integer in the range") { ----
1285 return Error(ErrorLoc, Msg + " [" + Twine(Lower) + ", " + Twine(Upper) + "]"); 0
1286 } ----
1287 ----
1288 bool RISCVAsmParser::generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1289 OperandVector &Operands, uint64_t ErrorInfo, int64_t Lower, int64_t Upper, ----
1290 const Twine &Msg = "immediate must be an integer in the range") { ----
1291 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1292 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(ErrorLoc, Lower, Upper, Msg); 0
1293 } ----
1294 ----
1295 bool RISCVAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode, 0
1296 OperandVector &Operands, ----
1297 MCStreamer &Out, ----
1298 uint64_t &ErrorInfo, ----
1299 bool MatchingInlineAsm) { ----
1300 MCInst Inst; 0
1301 FeatureBitset MissingFeatures; 0
1302 ----
1303 auto Result = MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, ErrorInfo, MissingFeatures, 0
1304 MatchingInlineAsm); ----
1305 switch (Result) { 0
1306 default: 0
1307 break; 0
1308 case Match_Success: 0
1309 if (validateInstruction(Inst, Operands)) 0
1310 return true; 0
1311 return processInstruction(Inst, IDLoc, Operands, Out); 0
1312 case Match_MissingFeature: { 0
1313 assert(MissingFeatures.any() && "Unknown missing features!"); 0
1314 bool FirstFeature = true; 0
1315 std::string Msg = "instruction requires the following:"; 0
1316 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MissingFeatures.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1317 if (MissingFeatures[i]) { 0
1318 Msg += FirstFeature ? " " : ", "; 0
1319 Msg += getSubtargetFeatureName(i); 0
1320 FirstFeature = false; 0
1321 } ----
1322 } ----
1323 return Error(IDLoc, Msg); 0
1324 } 0
1325 case Match_MnemonicFail: { 0
1326 FeatureBitset FBS = ComputeAvailableFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits()); 0
1327 std::string Suggestion = RISCVMnemonicSpellCheck( ----
1328 ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken(), FBS, 0); 0
1329 return Error(IDLoc, "unrecognized instruction mnemonic" + Suggestion); 0
1330 } 0
1331 case Match_InvalidOperand: { 0
1332 SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
1333 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL) { 0
1334 if (ErrorInfo >= Operands.size()) 0
1335 return Error(ErrorLoc, "too few operands for instruction"); 0
1336 ----
1337 ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1338 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc()) 0
1339 ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
1340 } ----
1341 return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid operand for instruction"); 0
1342 } ----
1343 } ----
1344 ----
1345 // Handle the case when the error message is of specific type ----
1346 // other than the generic Match_InvalidOperand, and the ----
1347 // corresponding operand is missing. ----
1348 if (Result > FIRST_TARGET_MATCH_RESULT_TY) { 0
1349 SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
1350 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL && ErrorInfo >= Operands.size()) 0
1351 return Error(ErrorLoc, "too few operands for instruction"); 0
1352 } ----
1353 ----
1354 switch (Result) { 0
1355 default: 0
1356 break; 0
1357 case Match_RequiresEvenGPRs: 0
1358 return Error(IDLoc, 0
1359 "double precision floating point operands must use even " ----
1360 "numbered X register"); 0
1361 case Match_InvalidImmXLenLI: 0
1362 if (isRV64()) { 0
1363 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1364 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand must be a constant 64-bit integer"); 0
1365 } ----
1366 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0
1367 std::numeric_limits::min(), 0
1368 std::numeric_limits::max()); 0
1369 case Match_InvalidImmXLenLI_Restricted: 0
1370 if (isRV64()) { 0
1371 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1372 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand either must be a constant 64-bit integer " 0
1373 "or a bare symbol name"); 0
1374 } ----
1375 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1376 Operands, ErrorInfo, std::numeric_limits::min(), 0
1377 std::numeric_limits::max(), 0
1378 "operand either must be a bare symbol name or an immediate integer in " ----
1379 "the range"); 0
1380 case Match_InvalidImmZero: { 0
1381 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1382 return Error(ErrorLoc, "immediate must be zero"); 0
1383 } ----
1384 case Match_InvalidUImmLog2XLen: 0
1385 if (isRV64()) 0
1386 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 6) - 1); 0
1387 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 5) - 1); 0
1388 case Match_InvalidUImmLog2XLenNonZero: 0
1389 if (isRV64()) 0
1390 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 1, (1 << 6) - 1); 0
1391 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 1, (1 << 5) - 1); 0
1392 case Match_InvalidUImmLog2XLenHalf: 0
1393 if (isRV64()) 0
1394 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 5) - 1); 0
1395 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 4) - 1); 0
1396 case Match_InvalidUImm1: 0
1397 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 1) - 1); 0
1398 case Match_InvalidUImm2: 0
1399 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 2) - 1); 0
1400 case Match_InvalidUImm2Lsb0: 0
1401 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, 2, 0
1402 "immediate must be one of"); 0
1403 case Match_InvalidUImm3: 0
1404 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 3) - 1); 0
1405 case Match_InvalidUImm4: 0
1406 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 4) - 1); 0
1407 case Match_InvalidUImm5: 0
1408 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 5) - 1); 0
1409 case Match_InvalidUImm6: 0
1410 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 6) - 1); 0
1411 case Match_InvalidUImm7: 0
1412 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 7) - 1); 0
1413 case Match_InvalidUImm8: 0
1414 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 8) - 1); 0
1415 case Match_InvalidUImm8GE32: 0
1416 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 32, (1 << 8) - 1); 0
1417 case Match_InvalidSImm5: 0
1418 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 4), 0
1419 (1 << 4) - 1); 0
1420 case Match_InvalidSImm6: 0
1421 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 5), 0
1422 (1 << 5) - 1); 0
1423 case Match_InvalidSImm6NonZero: 0
1424 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1425 Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 5), (1 << 5) - 1, ----
1426 "immediate must be non-zero in the range"); 0
1427 case Match_InvalidCLUIImm: 0
1428 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1429 Operands, ErrorInfo, 1, (1 << 5) - 1, ----
1430 "immediate must be in [0xfffe0, 0xfffff] or"); 0
1431 case Match_InvalidUImm7Lsb00: 0
1432 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1433 Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 7) - 4, ----
1434 "immediate must be a multiple of 4 bytes in the range"); 0
1435 case Match_InvalidUImm8Lsb00: 0
1436 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1437 Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 8) - 4, ----
1438 "immediate must be a multiple of 4 bytes in the range"); 0
1439 case Match_InvalidUImm8Lsb000: 0
1440 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1441 Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 8) - 8, ----
1442 "immediate must be a multiple of 8 bytes in the range"); 0
1443 case Match_InvalidSImm9Lsb0: 0
1444 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1445 Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 8), (1 << 8) - 2, ----
1446 "immediate must be a multiple of 2 bytes in the range"); 0
1447 case Match_InvalidUImm9Lsb000: 0
1448 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1449 Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 9) - 8, ----
1450 "immediate must be a multiple of 8 bytes in the range"); 0
1451 case Match_InvalidUImm10Lsb00NonZero: 0
1452 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1453 Operands, ErrorInfo, 4, (1 << 10) - 4, ----
1454 "immediate must be a multiple of 4 bytes in the range"); 0
1455 case Match_InvalidSImm10Lsb0000NonZero: 0
1456 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1457 Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 9), (1 << 9) - 16, ----
1458 "immediate must be a multiple of 16 bytes and non-zero in the range"); 0
1459 case Match_InvalidSImm12: 0
1460 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1461 Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 11), (1 << 11) - 1, ----
1462 "operand must be a symbol with %lo/%pcrel_lo/%tprel_lo modifier or an " ----
1463 "integer in the range"); 0
1464 case Match_InvalidSImm12Lsb0: 0
1465 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1466 Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 11), (1 << 11) - 2, ----
1467 "immediate must be a multiple of 2 bytes in the range"); 0
1468 case Match_InvalidSImm12Lsb00000: 0
1469 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1470 Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 11), (1 << 11) - 32, ----
1471 "immediate must be a multiple of 32 bytes in the range"); 0
1472 case Match_InvalidSImm13Lsb0: 0
1473 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1474 Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 12), (1 << 12) - 2, ----
1475 "immediate must be a multiple of 2 bytes in the range"); 0
1476 case Match_InvalidUImm20LUI: 0
1477 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 20) - 1, 0
1478 "operand must be a symbol with " ----
1479 "%hi/%tprel_hi modifier or an integer in " ----
1480 "the range"); 0
1481 case Match_InvalidUImm20AUIPC: 0
1482 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1483 Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 20) - 1, ----
1484 "operand must be a symbol with a " ----
1485 "%pcrel_hi/%got_pcrel_hi/%tls_ie_pcrel_hi/%tls_gd_pcrel_hi modifier or " ----
1486 "an integer in the range"); 0
1487 case Match_InvalidSImm21Lsb0JAL: 0
1488 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1489 Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 20), (1 << 20) - 2, ----
1490 "immediate must be a multiple of 2 bytes in the range"); 0
1491 case Match_InvalidCSRSystemRegister: { 0
1492 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, (1 << 12) - 1, 0
1493 "operand must be a valid system register " ----
1494 "name or an integer in the range"); 0
1495 } ----
1496 case Match_InvalidLoadFPImm: { 0
1497 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1498 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand must be a valid floating-point constant"); 0
1499 } ----
1500 case Match_InvalidBareSymbol: { 0
1501 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1502 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand must be a bare symbol name"); 0
1503 } ----
1504 case Match_InvalidPseudoJumpSymbol: { 0
1505 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1506 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand must be a valid jump target"); 0
1507 } ----
1508 case Match_InvalidCallSymbol: { 0
1509 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1510 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand must be a bare symbol name"); 0
1511 } ----
1512 case Match_InvalidTPRelAddSymbol: { 0
1513 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1514 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand must be a symbol with %tprel_add modifier"); 0
1515 } ----
1516 case Match_InvalidRTZArg: { 0
1517 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1518 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand must be 'rtz' floating-point rounding mode"); 0
1519 } ----
1520 case Match_InvalidVTypeI: { 0
1521 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1522 return generateVTypeError(ErrorLoc); 0
1523 } ----
1524 case Match_InvalidVMaskRegister: { 0
1525 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1526 return Error(ErrorLoc, "operand must be v0.t"); 0
1527 } ----
1528 case Match_InvalidSImm5Plus1: { 0
1529 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, -(1 << 4) + 1, 0
1530 (1 << 4), ----
1531 "immediate must be in the range"); 0
1532 } ----
1533 case Match_InvalidRlist: { 0
1534 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1535 return Error( 0
1536 ErrorLoc, ----
1537 "operand must be {ra [, s0[-sN]]} or {x1 [, x8[-x9][, x18[-xN]]]}"); 0
1538 } ----
1539 case Match_InvalidSpimm: { 0
1540 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
1541 return Error( 0
1542 ErrorLoc, ----
1543 "stack adjustment is invalid for this instruction and register list; " ----
1544 "refer to Zc spec for a detailed range of stack adjustment"); 0
1545 } ----
1546 case Match_InvalidRnumArg: { 0
1547 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(Operands, ErrorInfo, 0, 10); 0
1548 } ----
1549 } ----
1550 ----
1551 llvm_unreachable("Unknown match type detected!"); 0
1552 } 0
1553 ----
1554 // Attempts to match Name as a register (either using the default name or ----
1555 // alternative ABI names), setting RegNo to the matching register. Upon ----
1556 // failure, returns a non-valid MCRegister. If IsRVE, then registers x16-x31 ----
1557 // will be rejected. ----
1558 static MCRegister matchRegisterNameHelper(bool IsRVE, StringRef Name) { 0
1559 MCRegister Reg = MatchRegisterName(Name); 0
1560 // The 16-/32- and 64-bit FPRs have the same asm name. Check that the initial ----
1561 // match always matches the 64-bit variant, and not the 16/32-bit one. ----
1562 assert(!(Reg >= RISCV::F0_H && Reg <= RISCV::F31_H)); 0
1563 assert(!(Reg >= RISCV::F0_F && Reg <= RISCV::F31_F)); 0
1564 // The default FPR register class is based on the tablegen enum ordering. ----
1565 static_assert(RISCV::F0_D < RISCV::F0_H, "FPR matching must be updated"); ----
1566 static_assert(RISCV::F0_D < RISCV::F0_F, "FPR matching must be updated"); ----
1567 if (!Reg) 0
1568 Reg = MatchRegisterAltName(Name); 0
1569 if (IsRVE && Reg >= RISCV::X16 && Reg <= RISCV::X31) 0
1570 Reg = RISCV::NoRegister; 0
1571 return Reg; 0
1572 } ----
1573 ----
1574 bool RISCVAsmParser::parseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, 0
1575 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
1576 if (tryParseRegister(RegNo, StartLoc, EndLoc) != MatchOperand_Success) 0
1577 return Error(StartLoc, "invalid register name"); 0
1578 return false; 0
1579 } ----
1580 ----
1581 OperandMatchResultTy RISCVAsmParser::tryParseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, 0
1582 SMLoc &StartLoc, ----
1583 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
1584 const AsmToken &Tok = getParser().getTok(); 0
1585 StartLoc = Tok.getLoc(); 0
1586 EndLoc = Tok.getEndLoc(); 0
1587 StringRef Name = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
1588 ----
1589 RegNo = matchRegisterNameHelper(isRVE(), Name); 0
1590 if (!RegNo) 0
1591 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1592 ----
1593 getParser().Lex(); // Eat identifier token. 0
1594 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1595 } ----
1596 ----
1597 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseRegister(OperandVector &Operands, 0
1598 bool AllowParens) { ----
1599 SMLoc FirstS = getLoc(); 0
1600 bool HadParens = false; 0
1601 AsmToken LParen; 0
1602 ----
1603 // If this is an LParen and a parenthesised register name is allowed, parse it ----
1604 // atomically. ----
1605 if (AllowParens && getLexer().is(AsmToken::LParen)) { 0
1606 AsmToken Buf[2]; 0
1607 size_t ReadCount = getLexer().peekTokens(Buf); 0
1608 if (ReadCount == 2 && Buf[1].getKind() == AsmToken::RParen) { 0
1609 HadParens = true; 0
1610 LParen = getParser().getTok(); 0
1611 getParser().Lex(); // Eat '(' 0
1612 } ----
1613 } 0
1614 ----
1615 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1616 default: 0
1617 if (HadParens) 0
1618 getLexer().UnLex(LParen); 0
1619 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1620 case AsmToken::Identifier: 0
1621 StringRef Name = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
1622 MCRegister RegNo = matchRegisterNameHelper(isRVE(), Name); 0
1623 ----
1624 if (!RegNo) { 0
1625 if (HadParens) 0
1626 getLexer().UnLex(LParen); 0
1627 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1628 } ----
1629 if (HadParens) 0
1630 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createToken("(", FirstS)); 0
1631 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
1632 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() + Name.size()); 0
1633 getLexer().Lex(); 0
1634 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createReg(RegNo, S, E)); 0
1635 } ----
1636 ----
1637 if (HadParens) { 0
1638 getParser().Lex(); // Eat ')' 0
1639 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createToken(")", getLoc())); 0
1640 } ----
1641 ----
1642 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1643 } 0
1644 ----
1645 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseInsnDirectiveOpcode(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1646 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
1647 SMLoc E; 0
1648 const MCExpr *Res; ----
1649 ----
1650 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1651 default: 0
1652 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1653 case AsmToken::LParen: 0
1654 case AsmToken::Minus: ----
1655 case AsmToken::Plus: ----
1656 case AsmToken::Exclaim: ----
1657 case AsmToken::Tilde: ----
1658 case AsmToken::Integer: ----
1659 case AsmToken::String: { ----
1660 if (getParser().parseExpression(Res, E)) 0
1661 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1662 ----
1663 auto *CE = dyn_cast(Res); 0
1664 if (CE) { 0
1665 int64_t Imm = CE->getValue(); 0
1666 if (isUInt<7>(Imm)) { 0
1667 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
1668 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1669 } ----
1670 } ----
1671 ----
1672 break; 0
1673 } ----
1674 case AsmToken::Identifier: { 0
1675 StringRef Identifier; 0
1676 if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Identifier)) 0
1677 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1678 ----
1679 auto Opcode = RISCVInsnOpcode::lookupRISCVOpcodeByName(Identifier); 0
1680 if (Opcode) { 0
1681 assert(isUInt<7>(Opcode->Value) && (Opcode->Value & 0x3) == 3 && 0
1682 "Unexpected opcode"); ----
1683 Res = MCConstantExpr::create(Opcode->Value, getContext()); 0
1684 E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() + Identifier.size()); 0
1685 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
1686 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1687 } ----
1688 ----
1689 break; 0
1690 } ----
1691 case AsmToken::Percent: 0
1692 break; 0
1693 } ----
1694 ----
1695 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1696 S, 0, 127, ----
1697 "opcode must be a valid opcode name or an immediate in the range"); 0
1698 } ----
1699 ----
1700 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseInsnCDirectiveOpcode(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1701 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
1702 SMLoc E; 0
1703 const MCExpr *Res; ----
1704 ----
1705 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1706 default: 0
1707 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1708 case AsmToken::LParen: 0
1709 case AsmToken::Minus: ----
1710 case AsmToken::Plus: ----
1711 case AsmToken::Exclaim: ----
1712 case AsmToken::Tilde: ----
1713 case AsmToken::Integer: ----
1714 case AsmToken::String: { ----
1715 if (getParser().parseExpression(Res, E)) 0
1716 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1717 ----
1718 auto *CE = dyn_cast(Res); 0
1719 if (CE) { 0
1720 int64_t Imm = CE->getValue(); 0
1721 if (Imm >= 0 && Imm <= 2) { 0
1722 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
1723 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1724 } ----
1725 } ----
1726 ----
1727 break; 0
1728 } ----
1729 case AsmToken::Identifier: { 0
1730 StringRef Identifier; 0
1731 if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Identifier)) 0
1732 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1733 ----
1734 unsigned Opcode; ----
1735 if (Identifier == "C0") 0
1736 Opcode = 0; 0
1737 else if (Identifier == "C1") 0
1738 Opcode = 1; 0
1739 else if (Identifier == "C2") 0
1740 Opcode = 2; 0
1741 else ----
1742 break; 0
1743 ----
1744 Res = MCConstantExpr::create(Opcode, getContext()); 0
1745 E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() + Identifier.size()); 0
1746 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
1747 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1748 } ----
1749 case AsmToken::Percent: { 0
1750 // Discard operand with modifier. ----
1751 break; 0
1752 } ----
1753 } ----
1754 ----
1755 return generateImmOutOfRangeError( 0
1756 S, 0, 2, ----
1757 "opcode must be a valid opcode name or an immediate in the range"); 0
1758 } ----
1759 ----
1760 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseCSRSystemRegister(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1761 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
1762 const MCExpr *Res; ----
1763 ----
1764 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1765 default: 0
1766 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1767 case AsmToken::LParen: 0
1768 case AsmToken::Minus: ----
1769 case AsmToken::Plus: ----
1770 case AsmToken::Exclaim: ----
1771 case AsmToken::Tilde: ----
1772 case AsmToken::Integer: ----
1773 case AsmToken::String: { ----
1774 if (getParser().parseExpression(Res)) 0
1775 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1776 ----
1777 auto *CE = dyn_cast(Res); 0
1778 if (CE) { 0
1779 int64_t Imm = CE->getValue(); 0
1780 if (isUInt<12>(Imm)) { 0
1781 auto SysReg = RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByEncoding(Imm); 0
1782 // Accept an immediate representing a named or un-named Sys Reg ----
1783 // if the range is valid, regardless of the required features. ----
1784 Operands.push_back( 0
1785 RISCVOperand::createSysReg(SysReg ? SysReg->Name : "", S, Imm)); 0
1786 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1787 } ----
1788 } ----
1789 ----
1790 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(S, 0, (1 << 12) - 1); 0
1791 } ----
1792 case AsmToken::Identifier: { 0
1793 StringRef Identifier; 0
1794 if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Identifier)) 0
1795 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1796 ----
1797 // Check for CSR names conflicts. ----
1798 // Custom CSR names might conflict with CSR names in privileged spec. ----
1799 // E.g. - SiFive mnscratch(0x350) and privileged spec mnscratch(0x740). ----
1800 auto CheckCSRNameConflict = [&]() { 0
1801 if (!(RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName(Identifier))) { 0
1802 Error(S, "system register use requires an option to be enabled"); 0
1803 return true; 0
1804 } ----
1805 return false; 0
1806 }; 0
1807 ----
1808 // First check for vendor specific CSRs. ----
1809 auto SiFiveReg = RISCVSysReg::lookupSiFiveRegByName(Identifier); 0
1810 if (SiFiveReg) { 0
1811 if (SiFiveReg->haveVendorRequiredFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits())) { 0
1812 Operands.push_back( 0
1813 RISCVOperand::createSysReg(Identifier, S, SiFiveReg->Encoding)); 0
1814 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1815 } ----
1816 if (CheckCSRNameConflict()) 0
1817 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1818 } ----
1819 ----
1820 auto SysReg = RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByName(Identifier); 0
1821 if (!SysReg) 0
1822 if ((SysReg = RISCVSysReg::lookupSysRegByDeprecatedName(Identifier))) 0
1823 Warning(S, "'" + Identifier + "' is a deprecated alias for '" + 0
1824 SysReg->Name + "'"); 0
1825 ----
1826 // Check for CSR encoding conflicts. ----
1827 // Custom CSR encoding might conflict with CSR encoding in privileged spec. ----
1828 // E.g. - SiFive mnscratch(0x350) and privileged spec miselect(0x350). ----
1829 auto CheckCSREncodingConflict = [&]() { 0
1830 auto Reg = RISCVSysReg::lookupSiFiveRegByEncoding(SysReg->Encoding); 0
1831 if (Reg && Reg->haveVendorRequiredFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits())) { 0
1832 Warning(S, "'" + Identifier + "' CSR is not available on the current " + 0
1833 "subtarget. Instead '" + Reg->Name + 0
1834 "' CSR will be used."); 0
1835 Operands.push_back( 0
1836 RISCVOperand::createSysReg(Reg->Name, S, Reg->Encoding)); 0
1837 return true; 0
1838 } ----
1839 return false; 0
1840 }; 0
1841 ----
1842 // Accept a named SysReg if the required features are present. ----
1843 if (SysReg) { 0
1844 if (!SysReg->haveRequiredFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits())) 0
1845 return Error(S, "system register use requires an option to be enabled"); 0
1846 if (CheckCSREncodingConflict()) 0
1847 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1848 Operands.push_back( 0
1849 RISCVOperand::createSysReg(Identifier, S, SysReg->Encoding)); 0
1850 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1851 } ----
1852 ----
1853 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(S, 0, (1 << 12) - 1, 0
1854 "operand must be a valid system register " ----
1855 "name or an integer in the range"); 0
1856 } ----
1857 case AsmToken::Percent: { 0
1858 // Discard operand with modifier. ----
1859 return generateImmOutOfRangeError(S, 0, (1 << 12) - 1); 0
1860 } ----
1861 } ----
1862 ----
1863 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; ----
1864 } ----
1865 ----
1866 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseFPImm(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1867 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
1868 ----
1869 // Parse special floats (inf/nan/min) representation. ----
1870 if (getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) { 0
1871 StringRef Identifier = getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
1872 if (Identifier.compare_insensitive("inf") == 0) { 0
1873 Operands.push_back( 0
1874 RISCVOperand::createImm(MCConstantExpr::create(30, getContext()), S, 0
1875 getTok().getEndLoc(), isRV64())); 0
1876 } else if (Identifier.compare_insensitive("nan") == 0) { 0
1877 Operands.push_back( 0
1878 RISCVOperand::createImm(MCConstantExpr::create(31, getContext()), S, 0
1879 getTok().getEndLoc(), isRV64())); 0
1880 } else if (Identifier.compare_insensitive("min") == 0) { 0
1881 Operands.push_back( 0
1882 RISCVOperand::createImm(MCConstantExpr::create(1, getContext()), S, 0
1883 getTok().getEndLoc(), isRV64())); 0
1884 } else { ----
1885 return TokError("invalid floating point literal"); 0
1886 } ----
1887 ----
1888 Lex(); // Eat the token. 0
1889 ----
1890 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1891 } ----
1892 ----
1893 // Handle negation, as that still comes through as a separate token. ----
1894 bool IsNegative = parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Minus); 0
1895 ----
1896 const AsmToken &Tok = getTok(); 0
1897 if (!Tok.is(AsmToken::Real)) 0
1898 return TokError("invalid floating point immediate"); 0
1899 ----
1900 // Parse FP representation. ----
1901 APFloat RealVal(APFloat::IEEEdouble()); 0
1902 auto StatusOrErr = ----
1903 RealVal.convertFromString(Tok.getString(), APFloat::rmTowardZero); 0
1904 if (errorToBool(StatusOrErr.takeError())) 0
1905 return TokError("invalid floating point representation"); 0
1906 ----
1907 if (IsNegative) 0
1908 RealVal.changeSign(); 0
1909 ----
1910 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createFPImm( 0
1911 RealVal.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), S)); 0
1912 ----
1913 Lex(); // Eat the token. 0
1914 ----
1915 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1916 } 0
1917 ----
1918 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseImmediate(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1919 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
1920 SMLoc E; 0
1921 const MCExpr *Res; ----
1922 ----
1923 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
1924 default: 0
1925 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1926 case AsmToken::LParen: 0
1927 case AsmToken::Dot: ----
1928 case AsmToken::Minus: ----
1929 case AsmToken::Plus: ----
1930 case AsmToken::Exclaim: ----
1931 case AsmToken::Tilde: ----
1932 case AsmToken::Integer: ----
1933 case AsmToken::String: ----
1934 case AsmToken::Identifier: ----
1935 if (getParser().parseExpression(Res, E)) 0
1936 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1937 break; 0
1938 case AsmToken::Percent: 0
1939 return parseOperandWithModifier(Operands); 0
1940 } ----
1941 ----
1942 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
1943 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1944 } ----
1945 ----
1946 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseOperandWithModifier(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1947 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
1948 SMLoc E; 0
1949 ----
1950 if (parseToken(AsmToken::Percent, "expected '%' for operand modifier")) 0
1951 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1952 ----
1953 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Identifier) 0
1954 return Error(getLoc(), "expected valid identifier for operand modifier"); 0
1955 StringRef Identifier = getParser().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
1956 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VK = RISCVMCExpr::getVariantKindForName(Identifier); 0
1957 if (VK == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_Invalid) 0
1958 return Error(getLoc(), "unrecognized operand modifier"); 0
1959 ----
1960 getParser().Lex(); // Eat the identifier 0
1961 if (parseToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected '('")) 0
1962 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1963 ----
1964 const MCExpr *SubExpr; ----
1965 if (getParser().parseParenExpression(SubExpr, E)) 0
1966 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1967 ----
1968 const MCExpr *ModExpr = RISCVMCExpr::create(SubExpr, VK, getContext()); 0
1969 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(ModExpr, S, E, isRV64())); 0
1970 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
1971 } ----
1972 ----
1973 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseBareSymbol(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1974 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
1975 const MCExpr *Res; ----
1976 ----
1977 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Identifier) 0
1978 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1979 ----
1980 StringRef Identifier; 0
1981 AsmToken Tok = getLexer().getTok(); 0
1982 ----
1983 if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Identifier)) 0
1984 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
1985 ----
1986 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() + Identifier.size()); 0
1987 ----
1988 if (Identifier.consume_back("@plt")) 0
1989 return Error(getLoc(), "'@plt' operand not valid for instruction"); 0
1990 ----
1991 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Identifier); 0
1992 ----
1993 if (Sym->isVariable()) { 0
1994 const MCExpr *V = Sym->getVariableValue(/*SetUsed=*/false); 0
1995 if (!isa(V)) { 0
1996 getLexer().UnLex(Tok); // Put back if it's not a bare symbol. 0
1997 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1998 } ----
1999 Res = V; 0
2000 } else ----
2001 Res = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext()); 0
2002 ----
2003 MCBinaryExpr::Opcode Opcode; ----
2004 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
2005 default: 0
2006 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
2007 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2008 case AsmToken::Plus: 0
2009 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Add; 0
2010 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2011 break; 0
2012 case AsmToken::Minus: 0
2013 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Sub; 0
2014 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2015 break; 0
2016 } ----
2017 ----
2018 const MCExpr *Expr; ----
2019 if (getParser().parseExpression(Expr, E)) 0
2020 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2021 Res = MCBinaryExpr::create(Opcode, Res, Expr, getContext()); 0
2022 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
2023 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2024 } 0
2025 ----
2026 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseCallSymbol(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2027 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
2028 const MCExpr *Res; ----
2029 ----
2030 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Identifier) 0
2031 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
2032 ----
2033 // Avoid parsing the register in `call rd, foo` as a call symbol. ----
2034 if (getLexer().peekTok().getKind() != AsmToken::EndOfStatement) 0
2035 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
2036 ----
2037 StringRef Identifier; 0
2038 if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Identifier)) 0
2039 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2040 ----
2041 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() + Identifier.size()); 0
2042 ----
2043 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind Kind = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_CALL; 0
2044 if (Identifier.consume_back("@plt")) 0
2045 Kind = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_CALL_PLT; 0
2046 ----
2047 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Identifier); 0
2048 Res = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext()); 0
2049 Res = RISCVMCExpr::create(Res, Kind, getContext()); 0
2050 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
2051 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2052 } ----

2054 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parsePseudoJumpSymbol(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2055 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
2056 SMLoc E; 0
2057 const MCExpr *Res; ----
2058 ----
2059 if (getParser().parseExpression(Res, E)) 0
2060 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2061 ----
2062 if (Res->getKind() != MCExpr::ExprKind::SymbolRef || 0
2063 cast(Res)->getKind() == 0
2064 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind::VK_PLT) ----
2065 return Error(S, "operand must be a valid jump target"); 0
2066 ----
2067 Res = RISCVMCExpr::create(Res, RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_CALL, getContext()); 0
2068 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createImm(Res, S, E, isRV64())); 0
2069 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2070 } ----
2071 ----
2072 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseJALOffset(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2073 // Parsing jal operands is fiddly due to the `jal foo` and `jal ra, foo` ----
2074 // both being acceptable forms. When parsing `jal ra, foo` this function ----
2075 // will be called for the `ra` register operand in an attempt to match the ----
2076 // single-operand alias. parseJALOffset must fail for this case. It would ----
2077 // seem logical to try parse the operand using parseImmediate and return ----
2078 // NoMatch if the next token is a comma (meaning we must be parsing a jal in ----
2079 // the second form rather than the first). We can't do this as there's no ----
2080 // way of rewinding the lexer state. Instead, return NoMatch if this operand ----
2081 // is an identifier and is followed by a comma. ----
2082 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier) && 0
2083 getLexer().peekTok().is(AsmToken::Comma)) 0
2084 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
2085 ----
2086 return parseImmediate(Operands); 0
2087 } ----
2088 ----
2089 bool RISCVAsmParser::parseVTypeToken(StringRef Identifier, VTypeState &State, 0
2090 unsigned &Sew, unsigned &Lmul, ----
2091 bool &Fractional, bool &TailAgnostic, ----
2092 bool &MaskAgnostic) { ----
2093 switch (State) { 0
2094 case VTypeState_SEW: 0
2095 if (!Identifier.consume_front("e")) 0
2096 break; 0
2097 if (Identifier.getAsInteger(10, Sew)) 0
2098 break; 0
2099 if (!RISCVVType::isValidSEW(Sew)) 0
2100 break; 0
2101 State = VTypeState_LMUL; 0
2102 return false; 0
2103 case VTypeState_LMUL: { 0
2104 if (!Identifier.consume_front("m")) 0
2105 break; 0
2106 Fractional = Identifier.consume_front("f"); 0
2107 if (Identifier.getAsInteger(10, Lmul)) 0
2108 break; 0
2109 if (!RISCVVType::isValidLMUL(Lmul, Fractional)) 0
2110 break; 0
2111 State = VTypeState_TailPolicy; 0
2112 return false; 0
2113 } ----
2114 case VTypeState_TailPolicy: 0
2115 if (Identifier == "ta") 0
2116 TailAgnostic = true; 0
2117 else if (Identifier == "tu") 0
2118 TailAgnostic = false; 0
2119 else ----
2120 break; 0
2121 State = VTypeState_MaskPolicy; 0
2122 return false; 0
2123 case VTypeState_MaskPolicy: 0
2124 if (Identifier == "ma") 0
2125 MaskAgnostic = true; 0
2126 else if (Identifier == "mu") 0
2127 MaskAgnostic = false; 0
2128 else ----
2129 break; 0
2130 State = VTypeState_Done; 0
2131 return false; 0
2132 case VTypeState_Done: 0
2133 // Extra token? ----
2134 break; 0
2135 } ----
2136 ----
2137 return true; 0
2138 } ----

2140 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseVTypeI(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2141 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
2142 ----
2143 unsigned Sew = 0; 0
2144 unsigned Lmul = 0; 0
2145 bool Fractional = false; 0
2146 bool TailAgnostic = false; 0
2147 bool MaskAgnostic = false; 0
2148 ----
2149 VTypeState State = VTypeState_SEW; 0
2150 ----
2151 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2152 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
2153 ----
2154 StringRef Identifier = getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2155 ----
2156 if (parseVTypeToken(Identifier, State, Sew, Lmul, Fractional, TailAgnostic, 0
2157 MaskAgnostic)) ----
2158 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
2159 ----
2160 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2161 ----
2162 while (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
2163 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2164 break; 0
2165 ----
2166 Identifier = getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2167 ----
2168 if (parseVTypeToken(Identifier, State, Sew, Lmul, Fractional, TailAgnostic, 0
2169 MaskAgnostic)) ----
2170 break; 0
2171 ----
2172 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2173 } ----
2174 ----
2175 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement) && State == VTypeState_Done) { 0
2176 RISCVII::VLMUL VLMUL = RISCVVType::encodeLMUL(Lmul, Fractional); 0
2177 ----
2178 unsigned VTypeI = ----
2179 RISCVVType::encodeVTYPE(VLMUL, Sew, TailAgnostic, MaskAgnostic); 0
2180 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createVType(VTypeI, S)); 0
2181 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2182 } ----
2183 ----
2184 return generateVTypeError(S); 0
2185 } ----

2231 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseFRMArg(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2232 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2233 return TokError( 0

2235 ----
2236 StringRef Str = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2237 RISCVFPRndMode::RoundingMode FRM = RISCVFPRndMode::stringToRoundingMode(Str); 0
2238 ----
2239 if (FRM == RISCVFPRndMode::Invalid) 0
2240 return TokError( 0
2241 "operand must be a valid floating point rounding mode mnemonic"); 0
