2247 ----
2248 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseFenceArg(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2249 const AsmToken &Tok = getLexer().getTok(); 0
2250 ----
2251 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Integer)) { 0
2252 if (Tok.getIntVal() != 0) 0
2253 goto ParseFail; 0
2254 ----
2255 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createFenceArg(0, getLoc())); 0
2256 Lex(); 0
2257 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2258 } ----
2259 ----
2260 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) { 0
2261 StringRef Str = Tok.getIdentifier(); 0
2262 ----
2263 // Letters must be unique, taken from 'iorw', and in ascending order. This ----
2264 // holds as long as each individual character is one of 'iorw' and is ----
2265 // greater than the previous character. ----
2266 unsigned Imm = 0; 0
2267 bool Valid = true; 0
2268 char Prev = '\0'; 0
2269 for (char c : Str) { 0
2270 switch (c) { 0
2271 default: 0
2272 Valid = false; 0
2273 break; 0
2274 case 'i': 0
2275 Imm |= RISCVFenceField::I; 0
2276 break; 0
2277 case 'o': 0
2278 Imm |= RISCVFenceField::O; 0
2279 break; 0
2280 case 'r': 0
2281 Imm |= RISCVFenceField::R; 0
2282 break; 0
2283 case 'w': 0
2284 Imm |= RISCVFenceField::W; 0
2285 break; 0
2286 } ----
2287 ----
2288 if (c <= Prev) { 0
2289 Valid = false; 0
2290 break; 0
2291 } ----
2292 Prev = c; 0
2293 } ----
2294 ----
2295 if (!Valid) 0
2296 goto ParseFail; 0
2297 ----
2298 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createFenceArg(Imm, getLoc())); 0
2299 Lex(); 0
2300 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2301 } ----
2302 ----
2303 ParseFail: 0
2304 return TokError("operand must be formed of letters selected in-order from " 0
2305 "'iorw' or be 0"); 0
2306 } ----
2307 ----
2308 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseMemOpBaseReg(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2309 if (parseToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected '('")) 0
2310 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2311 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createToken("(", getLoc())); 0
2312 ----
2313 if (!parseRegister(Operands).isSuccess()) 0
2314 return Error(getLoc(), "expected register"); 0
2315 ----
2316 if (parseToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected ')'")) 0
2317 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2318 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createToken(")", getLoc())); 0
2319 ----
2320 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2321 } ----
2322 ----
2323 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseZeroOffsetMemOp(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2324 // Atomic operations such as lr.w, sc.w, and amo*.w accept a "memory operand" ----
2325 // as one of their register operands, such as `(a0)`. This just denotes that ----
2326 // the register (in this case `a0`) contains a memory address. ----
2327 // ----
2328 // Normally, we would be able to parse these by putting the parens into the ----
2329 // instruction string. However, GNU as also accepts a zero-offset memory ----
2330 // operand (such as `0(a0)`), and ignores the 0. Normally this would be parsed ----
2331 // with parseImmediate followed by parseMemOpBaseReg, but these instructions ----
2332 // do not accept an immediate operand, and we do not want to add a "dummy" ----
2333 // operand that is silently dropped. ----
2334 // ----
2335 // Instead, we use this custom parser. This will: allow (and discard) an ----
2336 // offset if it is zero; require (and discard) parentheses; and add only the ----
2337 // parsed register operand to `Operands`. ----
2338 // ----
2339 // These operands are printed with RISCVInstPrinter::printZeroOffsetMemOp, ----
2340 // which will only print the register surrounded by parentheses (which GNU as ----
2341 // also uses as its canonical representation for these operands). ----
2342 std::unique_ptr OptionalImmOp; 0
2343 ----
2344 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::LParen)) { 0
2345 // Parse an Integer token. We do not accept arbritrary constant expressions ----
2346 // in the offset field (because they may include parens, which complicates ----
2347 // parsing a lot). ----
2348 int64_t ImmVal; ----
2349 SMLoc ImmStart = getLoc(); 0
2350 if (getParser().parseIntToken(ImmVal, 0
2351 "expected '(' or optional integer offset")) ----
2352 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2353 ----
2354 // Create a RISCVOperand for checking later (so the error messages are ----
2355 // nicer), but we don't add it to Operands. ----
2356 SMLoc ImmEnd = getLoc(); 0
2357 OptionalImmOp = ----
2358 RISCVOperand::createImm(MCConstantExpr::create(ImmVal, getContext()), 0
2359 ImmStart, ImmEnd, isRV64()); 0
2360 } ----
2361 ----
2362 if (parseToken(AsmToken::LParen, 0
2363 OptionalImmOp ? "expected '(' after optional integer offset" ----
2364 : "expected '(' or optional integer offset")) 0
2365 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2366 ----
2367 if (!parseRegister(Operands).isSuccess()) 0
2368 return Error(getLoc(), "expected register"); 0
2369 ----
2370 if (parseToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected ')'")) 0
2371 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2372 ----
2373 // Deferred Handling of non-zero offsets. This makes the error messages nicer. ----
2374 if (OptionalImmOp && !OptionalImmOp->isImmZero()) 0
2375 return Error( 0
2376 OptionalImmOp->getStartLoc(), "optional integer offset must be 0", ----
2377 SMRange(OptionalImmOp->getStartLoc(), OptionalImmOp->getEndLoc())); 0
2378 ----
2379 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2380 } 0
2381 ----
2382 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseReglist(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2383 // Rlist: {ra [, s0[-sN]]} ----
2384 // XRlist: {x1 [, x8[-x9][, x18[-xN]]]} ----
2385 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
2386 ----
2387 if (parseToken(AsmToken::LCurly, "register list must start with '{'")) 0
2388 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2389 ----
2390 bool IsEABI = isRVE(); 0
2391 ----
2392 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2393 return Error(getLoc(), "register list must start from 'ra' or 'x1'"); 0
2394 ----
2395 StringRef RegName = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2396 MCRegister RegStart = matchRegisterNameHelper(IsEABI, RegName); 0
2397 MCRegister RegEnd; 0
2398 if (RegStart != RISCV::X1) 0
2399 return Error(getLoc(), "register list must start from 'ra' or 'x1'"); 0
2400 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2401 ----
2402 // parse case like ,s0 ----
2403 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
2404 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2405 return Error(getLoc(), "invalid register"); 0
2406 StringRef RegName = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2407 RegStart = matchRegisterNameHelper(IsEABI, RegName); 0
2408 if (!RegStart) 0
2409 return Error(getLoc(), "invalid register"); 0
2410 if (RegStart != RISCV::X8) 0
2411 return Error(getLoc(), 0
2412 "continuous register list must start from 's0' or 'x8'"); 0
2413 getLexer().Lex(); // eat reg 0
2414 } ----
2415 ----
2416 // parse case like -s1 ----
2417 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Minus)) { 0
2418 StringRef EndName = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2419 // FIXME: the register mapping and checks of EABI is wrong ----
2420 RegEnd = matchRegisterNameHelper(IsEABI, EndName); 0
2421 if (!RegEnd) 0
2422 return Error(getLoc(), "invalid register"); 0
2423 if (IsEABI && RegEnd != RISCV::X9) 0
2424 return Error(getLoc(), "contiguous register list of EABI can only be " 0
2425 "'s0-s1' or 'x8-x9' pair"); 0
2426 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2427 } ----
2428 ----
2429 if (!IsEABI) { 0
2430 // parse extra part like ', x18[-x20]' for XRegList ----
2431 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
2432 if (RegEnd != RISCV::X9) 0
2433 return Error( 0
2434 getLoc(), ----
2435 "first contiguous registers pair of register list must be 'x8-x9'"); 0
2436 ----
2437 // parse ', x18' for extra part ----
2438 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2439 return Error(getLoc(), "invalid register"); 0
2440 StringRef EndName = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2441 if (MatchRegisterName(EndName) != RISCV::X18) 0
2442 return Error(getLoc(), 0
2443 "second contiguous registers pair of register list " ----
2444 "must start from 'x18'"); 0
2445 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2446 ----
2447 // parse '-x20' for extra part ----
2448 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Minus)) { 0
2449 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2450 return Error(getLoc(), "invalid register"); 0
2451 EndName = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2452 if (MatchRegisterName(EndName) == RISCV::NoRegister) 0
2453 return Error(getLoc(), "invalid register"); 0
2454 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2455 } ----
2456 RegEnd = MatchRegisterName(EndName); 0
2457 } ----
2458 } ----
2459 ----
2460 if (RegEnd == RISCV::X26) 0
2461 return Error(getLoc(), "invalid register list, {ra, s0-s10} or {x1, x8-x9, " 0
2462 "x18-x26} is not supported"); 0
2463 ----
2464 if (parseToken(AsmToken::RCurly, "register list must end with '}'")) 0
2465 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
2466 ----
2467 if (RegEnd == RISCV::NoRegister) 0
2468 RegEnd = RegStart; 0
2469 ----
2470 auto Encode = RISCVZC::encodeRlist(RegEnd, IsEABI); 0
2471 if (Encode == 16) 0
2472 return Error(S, "invalid register list"); 0
2473 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createRlist(Encode, S)); 0
2474 ----
2475 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2476 } ----
2477 ----
2478 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseZcmpSpimm(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2479 (void)parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Minus); 0
2480 ----
2481 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
2482 int64_t StackAdjustment = getLexer().getTok().getIntVal(); 0
2483 unsigned Spimm = 0; 0
2484 unsigned RlistVal = static_cast(Operands[1].get())->Rlist.Val; 0
2485 ----
2486 bool IsEABI = isRVE(); 0
2487 if (!RISCVZC::getSpimm(RlistVal, Spimm, StackAdjustment, isRV64(), IsEABI)) 0
2488 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
2489 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createSpimm(Spimm << 4, S)); 0
2490 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2491 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
2492 } ----
2493 ----
2494 /// Looks at a token type and creates the relevant operand from this ----
2495 /// information, adding to Operands. If operand was parsed, returns false, else ----
2496 /// true. ----
2497 bool RISCVAsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Mnemonic) { 0
2498 // Check if the current operand has a custom associated parser, if so, try to ----
2499 // custom parse the operand, or fallback to the general approach. ----
2500 ParseStatus Result = ----
2501 MatchOperandParserImpl(Operands, Mnemonic, /*ParseForAllFeatures=*/true); 0
2502 if (Result.isSuccess()) 0
2503 return false; 0
2504 if (Result.isFailure()) 0
2505 return true; 0
2506 ----
2507 // Attempt to parse token as a register. ----
2508 if (parseRegister(Operands, true).isSuccess()) 0
2509 return false; 0
2510 ----
2511 // Attempt to parse token as an immediate ----
2512 if (parseImmediate(Operands).isSuccess()) { 0
2513 // Parse memory base register if present ----
2514 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LParen)) 0
2515 return !parseMemOpBaseReg(Operands).isSuccess(); 0
2516 return false; 0
2517 } ----
2518 ----
2519 // Finally we have exhausted all options and must declare defeat. ----
2520 Error(getLoc(), "unknown operand"); 0
2521 return true; 0
2522 } ----
2523 ----
2524 bool RISCVAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, 0
2525 StringRef Name, SMLoc NameLoc, ----
2526 OperandVector &Operands) { ----
2527 // Ensure that if the instruction occurs when relaxation is enabled, ----
2528 // relocations are forced for the file. Ideally this would be done when there ----
2529 // is enough information to reliably determine if the instruction itself may ----
2530 // cause relaxations. Unfortunately instruction processing stage occurs in the ----
2531 // same pass as relocation emission, so it's too late to set a 'sticky bit' ----
2532 // for the entire file. ----
2533 if (getSTI().hasFeature(RISCV::FeatureRelax)) { 0
2534 auto *Assembler = getTargetStreamer().getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr(); 0
2535 if (Assembler != nullptr) { 0
2536 RISCVAsmBackend &MAB = ----
2537 static_cast(Assembler->getBackend()); 0
2538 MAB.setForceRelocs(); 0
2539 } ----
2540 } ----
2541 ----
2542 // First operand is token for instruction ----
2543 Operands.push_back(RISCVOperand::createToken(Name, NameLoc)); 0
2544 ----
2545 // If there are no more operands, then finish ----
2546 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) { 0
2547 getParser().Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement. 0
2548 return false; 0
2549 } ----
2550 ----
2551 // Parse first operand ----
2552 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) 0
2553 return true; 0
2554 ----
2555 // Parse until end of statement, consuming commas between operands ----
2556 while (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
2557 // Parse next operand ----
2558 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) 0
2559 return true; 0
2560 } ----
2561 ----
2562 if (getParser().parseEOL("unexpected token")) { 0
2563 getParser().eatToEndOfStatement(); 0
2564 return true; 0
2565 } ----
2566 return false; 0
2567 } ----
2568 ----
2569 bool RISCVAsmParser::classifySymbolRef(const MCExpr *Expr, 0
2570 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind &Kind) { ----
2571 Kind = RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
2572 ----
2573 if (const RISCVMCExpr *RE = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
2574 Kind = RE->getKind(); 0
2575 Expr = RE->getSubExpr(); 0
2576 } ----
2577 ----
2578 MCValue Res; 0
2579 MCFixup Fixup; 0
2580 if (Expr->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, &Fixup)) 0
2581 return Res.getRefKind() == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None; 0
2582 return false; 0
2583 } ----
2584 ----
2585 bool RISCVAsmParser::isSymbolDiff(const MCExpr *Expr) { 0
2586 MCValue Res; 0
2587 MCFixup Fixup; 0
2588 if (Expr->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, &Fixup)) { 0
2589 return Res.getRefKind() == RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_None && Res.getSymA() && 0
2590 Res.getSymB(); 0
2591 } ----
2592 return false; 0
2593 } ----
2594 ----
2595 ParseStatus RISCVAsmParser::parseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) { 0
2596 StringRef IDVal = DirectiveID.getString(); 0
2597 ----
2598 if (IDVal == ".option") 0
2599 return parseDirectiveOption(); 0
2600 if (IDVal == ".attribute") 0
2601 return parseDirectiveAttribute(); 0
2602 if (IDVal == ".insn") 0
2603 return parseDirectiveInsn(DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
2604 if (IDVal == ".variant_cc") 0
2605 return parseDirectiveVariantCC(); 0
2606 ----
2607 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
2608 } ----
2609 ----
2610 bool RISCVAsmParser::resetToArch(StringRef Arch, SMLoc Loc, std::string &Result, 0
2611 bool FromOptionDirective) { ----
2612 for (auto Feature : RISCVFeatureKV) 0
2613 if (llvm::RISCVISAInfo::isSupportedExtensionFeature(Feature.Key)) 0
2614 clearFeatureBits(Feature.Value, Feature.Key); 0
2615 ----
2616 auto ParseResult = llvm::RISCVISAInfo::parseArchString( ----
2617 Arch, /*EnableExperimentalExtension=*/true, ----
2618 /*ExperimentalExtensionVersionCheck=*/true); 0
2619 if (!ParseResult) { 0
2620 std::string Buffer; 0
2621 raw_string_ostream OutputErrMsg(Buffer); 0
2622 handleAllErrors(ParseResult.takeError(), [&](llvm::StringError &ErrMsg) { 0
2623 OutputErrMsg << "invalid arch name '" << Arch << "', " 0
2624 << ErrMsg.getMessage(); 0
2625 }); 0
2626 ----
2627 return Error(Loc, OutputErrMsg.str()); 0
2628 } 0
2629 auto &ISAInfo = *ParseResult; 0
2630 ----
2631 for (auto Feature : RISCVFeatureKV) 0
2632 if (ISAInfo->hasExtension(Feature.Key)) 0
2633 setFeatureBits(Feature.Value, Feature.Key); 0
2634 ----
2635 if (FromOptionDirective) { 0
2636 if (ISAInfo->getXLen() == 32 && isRV64()) 0
2637 return Error(Loc, "bad arch string switching from rv64 to rv32"); 0
2638 else if (ISAInfo->getXLen() == 64 && !isRV64()) 0
2639 return Error(Loc, "bad arch string switching from rv32 to rv64"); 0
2640 } ----
2641 ----
2642 if (ISAInfo->getXLen() == 32) 0
2643 clearFeatureBits(RISCV::Feature64Bit, "64bit"); 0
2644 else if (ISAInfo->getXLen() == 64) 0
2645 setFeatureBits(RISCV::Feature64Bit, "64bit"); 0
2646 else ----
2647 return Error(Loc, "bad arch string " + Arch); 0
2648 ----
2649 Result = ISAInfo->toString(); 0
2650 return false; 0
2651 } 0
2652 ----
2653 bool RISCVAsmParser::parseDirectiveOption() { 0
2654 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2655 // Get the option token. ----
2656 AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
2657 ----
2658 // At the moment only identifiers are supported. ----
2659 if (parseToken(AsmToken::Identifier, "expected identifier")) 0
2660 return true; 0
2661 ----
2662 StringRef Option = Tok.getIdentifier(); 0
2663 ----
2664 if (Option == "push") { 0
2665 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2666 return true; 0
2667 ----
2668 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionPush(); 0
2669 pushFeatureBits(); 0
2670 return false; 0
2671 } ----
2672 ----
2673 if (Option == "pop") { 0
2674 SMLoc StartLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2675 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2676 return true; 0
2677 ----
2678 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionPop(); 0
2679 if (popFeatureBits()) 0
2680 return Error(StartLoc, ".option pop with no .option push"); 0
2681 ----
2682 return false; 0
2683 } ----
2684 ----
2685 if (Option == "arch") { 0
2686 SmallVector Args; 0
2687 do { ----
2688 if (Parser.parseComma()) 0
2689 return true; 0
2690 ----
2691 RISCVOptionArchArgType Type; ----
2692 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Plus)) 0
2693 Type = RISCVOptionArchArgType::Plus; 0
2694 else if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Minus)) 0
2695 Type = RISCVOptionArchArgType::Minus; 0
2696 else if (!Args.empty()) 0
2697 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), 0
2698 "unexpected token, expected + or -"); 0
2699 else ----
2700 Type = RISCVOptionArchArgType::Full; 0
2701 ----
2702 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2703 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), 0
2704 "unexpected token, expected identifier"); 0
2705 ----
2706 StringRef Arch = Parser.getTok().getString(); 0
2707 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2708 Parser.Lex(); 0
2709 ----
2710 if (Type == RISCVOptionArchArgType::Full) { 0
2711 std::string Result; 0
2712 if (resetToArch(Arch, Loc, Result, true)) 0
2713 return true; 0
2714 ----
2715 Args.emplace_back(Type, Result); 0
2716 break; 0
2717 } 0
2718 ----
2719 ArrayRef KVArray(RISCVFeatureKV); 0
2720 auto Ext = llvm::lower_bound(KVArray, Arch); 0
2721 if (Ext == KVArray.end() || StringRef(Ext->Key) != Arch || 0
2722 !RISCVISAInfo::isSupportedExtension(Arch)) { 0
2723 if (isDigit(Arch.back())) 0
2724 return Error( 0
2725 Loc, ----
2726 "Extension version number parsing not currently implemented"); 0
2727 return Error(Loc, "unknown extension feature"); 0
2728 } ----
2729 ----
2730 Args.emplace_back(Type, Ext->Key); 0
2731 ----
2732 if (Type == RISCVOptionArchArgType::Plus) { 0
2733 FeatureBitset OldFeatureBits = STI->getFeatureBits(); 0
2734 ----
2735 setFeatureBits(Ext->Value, Ext->Key); 0
2736 auto ParseResult = RISCVFeatures::parseFeatureBits(isRV64(), STI->getFeatureBits()); 0
2737 if (!ParseResult) { 0
2738 copySTI().setFeatureBits(OldFeatureBits); 0
2739 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(OldFeatureBits)); 0
2740 ----
2741 std::string Buffer; 0
2742 raw_string_ostream OutputErrMsg(Buffer); 0
2743 handleAllErrors(ParseResult.takeError(), [&](llvm::StringError &ErrMsg) { 0
2744 OutputErrMsg << ErrMsg.getMessage(); 0
2745 }); 0
2746 ----
2747 return Error(Loc, OutputErrMsg.str()); 0
2748 } 0
2749 } else { 0
2750 assert(Type == RISCVOptionArchArgType::Minus); 0
2751 // It is invalid to disable an extension that there are other enabled ----
2752 // extensions depend on it. ----
2753 // TODO: Make use of RISCVISAInfo to handle this ----
2754 for (auto Feature : KVArray) { 0
2755 if (getSTI().hasFeature(Feature.Value) && 0
2756 Feature.Implies.test(Ext->Value)) 0
2757 return Error(Loc, 0
2758 Twine("Can't disable ") + Ext->Key + " extension, " + 0
2759 Feature.Key + " extension requires " + Ext->Key + 0
2760 " extension be enabled"); 0
2761 } ----
2762 ----
2763 clearFeatureBits(Ext->Value, Ext->Key); 0
2764 } ----
2765 } while (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)); 0
2766 ----
2767 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2768 return true; 0
2769 ----
2770 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionArch(Args); 0
2771 return false; 0
2772 } 0
2773 ----
2774 if (Option == "rvc") { 0
2775 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2776 return true; 0
2777 ----
2778 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionRVC(); 0
2779 setFeatureBits(RISCV::FeatureStdExtC, "c"); 0
2780 return false; 0
2781 } ----
2782 ----
2783 if (Option == "norvc") { 0
2784 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2785 return true; 0
2786 ----
2787 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionNoRVC(); 0
2788 clearFeatureBits(RISCV::FeatureStdExtC, "c"); 0
2789 clearFeatureBits(RISCV::FeatureStdExtZca, "+zca"); 0
2790 return false; 0
2791 } ----
2792 ----
2793 if (Option == "pic") { 0
2794 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2795 return true; 0
2796 ----
2797 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionPIC(); 0
2798 ParserOptions.IsPicEnabled = true; 0
2799 return false; 0
2800 } ----
2801 ----
2802 if (Option == "nopic") { 0
2803 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2804 return true; 0
2805 ----
2806 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionNoPIC(); 0
2807 ParserOptions.IsPicEnabled = false; 0
2808 return false; 0
2809 } ----
2810 ----
2811 if (Option == "relax") { 0
2812 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2813 return true; 0
2814 ----
2815 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionRelax(); 0
2816 setFeatureBits(RISCV::FeatureRelax, "relax"); 0
2817 return false; 0
2818 } ----
2819 ----
2820 if (Option == "norelax") { 0
2821 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2822 return true; 0
2823 ----
2824 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionNoRelax(); 0
2825 clearFeatureBits(RISCV::FeatureRelax, "relax"); 0
2826 return false; 0
2827 } ----
2828 ----
2829 // Unknown option. ----
2830 Warning(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "unknown option, expected 'push', 'pop', " 0
2831 "'rvc', 'norvc', 'arch', 'relax' or " ----
2832 "'norelax'"); ----
2833 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement(); 0
2834 return false; 0
2835 } 0
2836 ----
2837 /// parseDirectiveAttribute ----
2838 /// ::= .attribute expression ',' ( expression | "string" ) ----
2839 /// ::= .attribute identifier ',' ( expression | "string" ) ----
2840 bool RISCVAsmParser::parseDirectiveAttribute() { 0
2841 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2842 int64_t Tag; ----
2843 SMLoc TagLoc; 0
2844 TagLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2845 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) { 0
2846 StringRef Name = Parser.getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
2847 std::optional Ret = ----
2848 ELFAttrs::attrTypeFromString(Name, RISCVAttrs::getRISCVAttributeTags()); 0
2849 if (!Ret) 0
2850 return Error(TagLoc, "attribute name not recognised: " + Name); 0
2851 Tag = *Ret; 0
2852 Parser.Lex(); 0
2853 } else { ----
2854 const MCExpr *AttrExpr; ----
2855 ----
2856 TagLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2857 if (Parser.parseExpression(AttrExpr)) 0
2858 return true; 0
2859 ----
2860 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(AttrExpr); 0
2861 if (check(!CE, TagLoc, "expected numeric constant")) 0
2862 return true; 0
2863 ----
2864 Tag = CE->getValue(); 0
2865 } ----
2866 ----
2867 if (Parser.parseComma()) 0
2868 return true; 0
2869 ----
2870 StringRef StringValue; 0
2871 int64_t IntegerValue = 0; 0
2872 bool IsIntegerValue = true; 0
2873 ----
2874 // RISC-V attributes have a string value if the tag number is odd ----
2875 // and an integer value if the tag number is even. ----
2876 if (Tag % 2) 0
2877 IsIntegerValue = false; 0
2878 ----
2879 SMLoc ValueExprLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2880 if (IsIntegerValue) { 0
2881 const MCExpr *ValueExpr; ----
2882 if (Parser.parseExpression(ValueExpr)) 0
2883 return true; 0
2884 ----
2885 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(ValueExpr); 0
2886 if (!CE) 0
2887 return Error(ValueExprLoc, "expected numeric constant"); 0
2888 IntegerValue = CE->getValue(); 0
2889 } else { ----
2890 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String)) 0
2891 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "expected string constant"); 0
2892 ----
2893 StringValue = Parser.getTok().getStringContents(); 0
2894 Parser.Lex(); 0
2895 } ----
2896 ----
2897 if (Parser.parseEOL()) 0
2898 return true; 0
2899 ----
2900 if (IsIntegerValue) 0
2901 getTargetStreamer().emitAttribute(Tag, IntegerValue); 0
2902 else if (Tag != RISCVAttrs::ARCH) 0
2903 getTargetStreamer().emitTextAttribute(Tag, StringValue); 0
2904 else { ----
2905 std::string Result; 0
2906 if (resetToArch(StringValue, ValueExprLoc, Result, false)) 0
2907 return true; 0
2908 ----
2909 // Then emit the arch string. ----
2910 getTargetStreamer().emitTextAttribute(Tag, Result); 0
2911 } 0
2912 ----
2913 return false; 0
2914 } ----
2915 ----
2916 bool isValidInsnFormat(StringRef Format, bool AllowC) { 0
2917 return StringSwitch(Format) 0
2918 .Cases("r", "r4", "i", "b", "sb", "u", "j", "uj", "s", true) 0
2919 .Cases("cr", "ci", "ciw", "css", "cl", "cs", "ca", "cb", "cj", AllowC) 0
2920 .Default(false); 0
2921 } ----
2922 ----
2923 /// parseDirectiveInsn ----
2924 /// ::= .insn [ format encoding, (operands (, operands)*) ] ----
2925 bool RISCVAsmParser::parseDirectiveInsn(SMLoc L) { 0
2926 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2927 ----
2928 // Expect instruction format as identifier. ----
2929 StringRef Format; 0
2930 SMLoc ErrorLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2931 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Format)) 0
2932 return Error(ErrorLoc, "expected instruction format"); 0
2933 ----
2934 bool AllowC = getSTI().hasFeature(RISCV::FeatureStdExtC) || 0
2935 getSTI().hasFeature(RISCV::FeatureStdExtZca); 0
2936 if (!isValidInsnFormat(Format, AllowC)) 0
2937 return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid instruction format"); 0
2938 ----
2939 std::string FormatName = (".insn_" + Format).str(); 0
2940 ----
2941 ParseInstructionInfo Info; 0
2942 SmallVector, 8> Operands; 0
2943 ----
2944 if (ParseInstruction(Info, FormatName, L, Operands)) 0
2945 return true; 0
2946 ----
2947 unsigned Opcode; ----
2948 uint64_t ErrorInfo; ----
2949 return MatchAndEmitInstruction(L, Opcode, Operands, Parser.getStreamer(), 0
2950 ErrorInfo, ----
2951 /*MatchingInlineAsm=*/false); 0
2952 } 0
2953 ----
2954 /// parseDirectiveVariantCC ----
2955 /// ::= .variant_cc symbol ----
2956 bool RISCVAsmParser::parseDirectiveVariantCC() { 0
2957 StringRef Name; 0
2958 if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Name)) 0
2959 return TokError("expected symbol name"); 0
2960 if (parseEOL()) 0
2961 return true; 0
2962 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveVariantCC( 0
2963 *getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name)); 0
2964 return false; 0
2965 } ----
2966 ----
2967 void RISCVAsmParser::emitToStreamer(MCStreamer &S, const MCInst &Inst) { 0
2968 MCInst CInst; 0
2969 bool Res = RISCVRVC::compress(CInst, Inst, getSTI()); 0
2970 if (Res) 0
2971 ++RISCVNumInstrsCompressed; 0
2972 S.emitInstruction((Res ? CInst : Inst), getSTI()); 0
2973 } 0
2974 ----
2975 void RISCVAsmParser::emitLoadImm(MCRegister DestReg, int64_t Value, 0
2976 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
2977 RISCVMatInt::InstSeq Seq = ----
2978 RISCVMatInt::generateInstSeq(Value, getSTI().getFeatureBits()); 0
2979 ----
2980 MCRegister SrcReg = RISCV::X0; 0
2981 for (const RISCVMatInt::Inst &Inst : Seq) { 0
2982 switch (Inst.getOpndKind()) { 0
2983 case RISCVMatInt::Imm: 0
2984 emitToStreamer(Out, 0
2985 MCInstBuilder(Inst.getOpcode()).addReg(DestReg).addImm(Inst.getImm())); 0
2986 break; 0
2987 case RISCVMatInt::RegX0: 0
2988 emitToStreamer( 0
2989 Out, MCInstBuilder(Inst.getOpcode()).addReg(DestReg).addReg(SrcReg).addReg( 0
2990 RISCV::X0)); ----
2991 break; 0
2992 case RISCVMatInt::RegReg: 0
2993 emitToStreamer( 0
2994 Out, MCInstBuilder(Inst.getOpcode()).addReg(DestReg).addReg(SrcReg).addReg( 0
2995 SrcReg)); ----
2996 break; 0
2997 case RISCVMatInt::RegImm: 0
2998 emitToStreamer( 0
2999 Out, MCInstBuilder(Inst.getOpcode()).addReg(DestReg).addReg(SrcReg).addImm( 0
3000 Inst.getImm())); ----
3001 break; 0
3002 } ----
3003 ----
3004 // Only the first instruction has X0 as its source. ----
3005 SrcReg = DestReg; 0
3006 } ----
3007 } 0
3008 ----
3009 void RISCVAsmParser::emitAuipcInstPair(MCOperand DestReg, MCOperand TmpReg, 0
3010 const MCExpr *Symbol, ----
3011 RISCVMCExpr::VariantKind VKHi, ----
3012 unsigned SecondOpcode, SMLoc IDLoc, ----
3013 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
3014 // A pair of instructions for PC-relative addressing; expands to ----
3015 // TmpLabel: AUIPC TmpReg, VKHi(symbol) ----
3016 // OP DestReg, TmpReg, %pcrel_lo(TmpLabel) ----
3017 MCContext &Ctx = getContext(); 0
3018 ----
3019 MCSymbol *TmpLabel = Ctx.createNamedTempSymbol("pcrel_hi"); 0
3020 Out.emitLabel(TmpLabel); 0
3021 ----
3022 const RISCVMCExpr *SymbolHi = RISCVMCExpr::create(Symbol, VKHi, Ctx); 0
3023 emitToStreamer( 0
3024 Out, MCInstBuilder(RISCV::AUIPC).addOperand(TmpReg).addExpr(SymbolHi)); 0
3025 ----
3026 const MCExpr *RefToLinkTmpLabel = ----
3027 RISCVMCExpr::create(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TmpLabel, Ctx), 0
3028 RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_PCREL_LO, Ctx); 0
3029 ----
3030 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(SecondOpcode) 0
3031 .addOperand(DestReg) 0
3032 .addOperand(TmpReg) 0
3033 .addExpr(RefToLinkTmpLabel)); 0
3034 } 0
3035 ----
3036 void RISCVAsmParser::emitLoadLocalAddress(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
3037 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
3038 // The load local address pseudo-instruction "lla" is used in PC-relative ----
3039 // addressing of local symbols: ----
3040 // lla rdest, symbol ----
3041 // expands to ----
3042 // TmpLabel: AUIPC rdest, %pcrel_hi(symbol) ----
3043 // ADDI rdest, rdest, %pcrel_lo(TmpLabel) ----
3044 MCOperand DestReg = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
3045 const MCExpr *Symbol = Inst.getOperand(1).getExpr(); 0
3046 emitAuipcInstPair(DestReg, DestReg, Symbol, RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_PCREL_HI, 0
3047 RISCV::ADDI, IDLoc, Out); ----
3048 } 0
3049 ----
3050 void RISCVAsmParser::emitLoadGlobalAddress(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
3051 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
3052 // The load global address pseudo-instruction "lga" is used in GOT-indirect ----
3053 // addressing of global symbols: ----
3054 // lga rdest, symbol ----
3055 // expands to ----
3056 // TmpLabel: AUIPC rdest, %got_pcrel_hi(symbol) ----
3057 // Lx rdest, %pcrel_lo(TmpLabel)(rdest) ----
3058 MCOperand DestReg = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
3059 const MCExpr *Symbol = Inst.getOperand(1).getExpr(); 0
3060 unsigned SecondOpcode = isRV64() ? RISCV::LD : RISCV::LW; 0
3061 emitAuipcInstPair(DestReg, DestReg, Symbol, RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_GOT_HI, 0
3062 SecondOpcode, IDLoc, Out); ----
3063 } 0
3064 ----
3065 void RISCVAsmParser::emitLoadAddress(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
3066 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
3067 // The load address pseudo-instruction "la" is used in PC-relative and ----
3068 // GOT-indirect addressing of global symbols: ----
3069 // la rdest, symbol ----
3070 // is an alias for either (for non-PIC) ----
3071 // lla rdest, symbol ----
3072 // or (for PIC) ----
3073 // lga rdest, symbol ----
3074 if (ParserOptions.IsPicEnabled) 0
3075 emitLoadGlobalAddress(Inst, IDLoc, Out); 0
3076 else ----
3077 emitLoadLocalAddress(Inst, IDLoc, Out); 0
3078 } 0

3080 void RISCVAsmParser::emitLoadTLSIEAddress(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, 0

3087 // Lx rdest, %pcrel_lo(TmpLabel)(rdest) ----
3088 MCOperand DestReg = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
3089 const MCExpr *Symbol = Inst.getOperand(1).getExpr(); 0
3090 unsigned SecondOpcode = isRV64() ? RISCV::LD : RISCV::LW; 0
3091 emitAuipcInstPair(DestReg, DestReg, Symbol, RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_TLS_GOT_HI, 0
3092 SecondOpcode, IDLoc, Out); ----
3093 } 0

3095 void RISCVAsmParser::emitLoadTLSGDAddress(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
3096 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
3097 // The load TLS GD address pseudo-instruction "la.tls.gd" is used in ----

3099 // la.tls.gd rdest, symbol ----
3100 // expands to ----

3108 ----
3109 void RISCVAsmParser::emitLoadStoreSymbol(MCInst &Inst, unsigned Opcode, 0
3110 SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out, ----
3111 bool HasTmpReg) { ----
3112 // The load/store pseudo-instruction does a pc-relative load with ----
3113 // a symbol. ----
3114 // ----
3115 // The expansion looks like this ----
3116 // ----
3117 // TmpLabel: AUIPC tmp, %pcrel_hi(symbol) ----
3118 // [S|L]X rd, %pcrel_lo(TmpLabel)(tmp) ----
3119 unsigned DestRegOpIdx = HasTmpReg ? 1 : 0; 0
3120 MCOperand DestReg = Inst.getOperand(DestRegOpIdx); 0
3121 unsigned SymbolOpIdx = HasTmpReg ? 2 : 1; 0
3122 MCOperand TmpReg = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
3123 const MCExpr *Symbol = Inst.getOperand(SymbolOpIdx).getExpr(); 0
3124 emitAuipcInstPair(DestReg, TmpReg, Symbol, RISCVMCExpr::VK_RISCV_PCREL_HI, 0
3125 Opcode, IDLoc, Out); ----
3126 } 0
3127 ----
3128 void RISCVAsmParser::emitPseudoExtend(MCInst &Inst, bool SignExtend, 0
3129 int64_t Width, SMLoc IDLoc, ----
3130 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
3131 // The sign/zero extend pseudo-instruction does two shifts, with the shift ----
3132 // amounts dependent on the XLEN. ----
3133 // ----
3134 // The expansion looks like this ----
3135 // ----
3136 // SLLI rd, rs, XLEN - Width ----
3137 // SR[A|R]I rd, rd, XLEN - Width ----
3138 MCOperand DestReg = Inst.getOperand(0); 0
3139 MCOperand SourceReg = Inst.getOperand(1); 0
3140 ----
3141 unsigned SecondOpcode = SignExtend ? RISCV::SRAI : RISCV::SRLI; 0
3142 int64_t ShAmt = (isRV64() ? 64 : 32) - Width; 0
3143 ----
3144 assert(ShAmt > 0 && "Shift amount must be non-zero."); 0
3145 ----
3146 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(RISCV::SLLI) 0
3147 .addOperand(DestReg) 0
3148 .addOperand(SourceReg) 0
3149 .addImm(ShAmt)); 0
3150 ----
3151 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(SecondOpcode) 0
3152 .addOperand(DestReg) 0
3153 .addOperand(DestReg) 0
3154 .addImm(ShAmt)); 0
3155 } 0
3156 ----
3157 void RISCVAsmParser::emitVMSGE(MCInst &Inst, unsigned Opcode, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
3158 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
3159 if (Inst.getNumOperands() == 3) { 0
3160 // unmasked va >= x ----
3161 // ----
3162 // pseudoinstruction: vmsge{u}.vx vd, va, x ----
3163 // expansion: vmslt{u}.vx vd, va, x; vmnand.mm vd, vd, vd ----
3164 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(Opcode) 0
3165 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3166 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)) 0
3167 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)) 0
3168 .addReg(RISCV::NoRegister)); 0
3169 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(RISCV::VMNAND_MM) 0
3170 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3171 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3172 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0))); 0
3173 } else if (Inst.getNumOperands() == 4) { 0
3174 // masked va >= x, vd != v0 ----
3175 // ----
3176 // pseudoinstruction: vmsge{u}.vx vd, va, x, v0.t ----
3177 // expansion: vmslt{u}.vx vd, va, x, v0.t; vmxor.mm vd, vd, v0 ----
3178 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != RISCV::V0 && 0
3179 "The destination register should not be V0."); ----
3180 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(Opcode) 0
3181 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3182 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)) 0
3183 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)) 0
3184 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3))); 0
3185 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(RISCV::VMXOR_MM) 0
3186 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3187 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3188 .addReg(RISCV::V0)); 0
3189 } else if (Inst.getNumOperands() == 5 && 0
3190 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == RISCV::V0) { 0
3191 // masked va >= x, vd == v0 ----
3192 // ----
3193 // pseudoinstruction: vmsge{u}.vx vd, va, x, v0.t, vt ----
3194 // expansion: vmslt{u}.vx vt, va, x; vmandn.mm vd, vd, vt ----
3195 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == RISCV::V0 && 0
3196 "The destination register should be V0."); ----
3197 assert(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() != RISCV::V0 && 0
3198 "The temporary vector register should not be V0."); ----
3199 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(Opcode) 0
3200 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)) 0
3201 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)) 0
3202 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)) 0
3203 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4))); 0
3204 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(RISCV::VMANDN_MM) 0
3205 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3206 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3207 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1))); 0
3208 } else if (Inst.getNumOperands() == 5) { 0
3209 // masked va >= x, any vd ----
3210 // ----
3211 // pseudoinstruction: vmsge{u}.vx vd, va, x, v0.t, vt ----
3212 // expansion: vmslt{u}.vx vt, va, x; vmandn.mm vt, v0, vt; vmandn.mm vd, ----
3213 // vd, v0; vmor.mm vd, vt, vd ----
3214 assert(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() != RISCV::V0 && 0
3215 "The temporary vector register should not be V0."); ----
3216 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(Opcode) 0
3217 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)) 0
3218 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)) 0
3219 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)) 0
3220 .addReg(RISCV::NoRegister)); 0
3221 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(RISCV::VMANDN_MM) 0
3222 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)) 0
3223 .addReg(RISCV::V0) 0
3224 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1))); 0
3225 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(RISCV::VMANDN_MM) 0
3226 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3227 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3228 .addReg(RISCV::V0)); 0
3229 emitToStreamer(Out, MCInstBuilder(RISCV::VMOR_MM) 0
3230 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)) 0
3231 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)) 0
3232 .addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0))); 0
3233 } ----
3234 } 0
3235 ----
3236 bool RISCVAsmParser::checkPseudoAddTPRel(MCInst &Inst, 0
3237 OperandVector &Operands) { ----
3238 assert(Inst.getOpcode() == RISCV::PseudoAddTPRel && "Invalid instruction"); 0
3239 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isReg() && "Unexpected second operand kind"); 0
3240 if (Inst.getOperand(2).getReg() != RISCV::X4) { 0
3241 SMLoc ErrorLoc = ((RISCVOperand &)*Operands[3]).getStartLoc(); 0
3242 return Error(ErrorLoc, "the second input operand must be tp/x4 when using " 0
3243 "%tprel_add modifier"); 0
3244 } ----
3245 ----
3246 return false; 0
3247 } ----

3249 std::unique_ptr RISCVAsmParser::defaultMaskRegOp() const { 0
3250 return RISCVOperand::createReg(RISCV::NoRegister, llvm::SMLoc(), 0
3251 llvm::SMLoc()); 0
3252 } ----
3253 ----
3254 std::unique_ptr RISCVAsmParser::defaultFRMArgOp() const { 0
3255 return RISCVOperand::createFRMArg(RISCVFPRndMode::RoundingMode::DYN, 0
3256 llvm::SMLoc()); 0
3257 } ----
3258 ----
3259 bool RISCVAsmParser::validateInstruction(MCInst &Inst, 0
3260 OperandVector &Operands) { ----
3261 unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode(); 0
3262 ----
3263 if (Opcode == RISCV::PseudoVMSGEU_VX_M_T || 0
3264 Opcode == RISCV::PseudoVMSGE_VX_M_T) { ----
3265 unsigned DestReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3266 unsigned TempReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3267 if (DestReg == TempReg) { 0
3268 SMLoc Loc = Operands.back()->getStartLoc(); 0
3269 return Error(Loc, "The temporary vector register cannot be the same as " 0
3270 "the destination register."); 0
3271 } ----
3272 } ----
3273 ----
3274 if (Opcode == RISCV::TH_LDD || Opcode == RISCV::TH_LWUD || 0
3275 Opcode == RISCV::TH_LWD) { ----
3276 unsigned Rd1 = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3277 unsigned Rd2 = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3278 unsigned Rs1 = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
3279 // The encoding with rd1 == rd2 == rs1 is reserved for XTHead load pair. ----
3280 if (Rs1 == Rd1 && Rs1 == Rd2) { 0
3281 SMLoc Loc = Operands[1]->getStartLoc(); 0
3282 return Error(Loc, "The source register and destination registers " 0
3283 "cannot be equal."); 0
3284 } ----
3285 } ----
3286 ----
3287 if (Opcode == RISCV::CM_MVSA01) { 0
3288 unsigned Rd1 = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3289 unsigned Rd2 = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3290 if (Rd1 == Rd2) { 0
3291 SMLoc Loc = Operands[1]->getStartLoc(); 0
3292 return Error(Loc, "'rs1' and 'rs2' must be different."); 0
3293 } ----
3294 } ----
3295 ----
3296 bool IsTHeadMemPair32 = (Opcode == RISCV::TH_LWD || 0
3297 Opcode == RISCV::TH_LWUD || Opcode == RISCV::TH_SWD); 0
3298 bool IsTHeadMemPair64 = (Opcode == RISCV::TH_LDD || Opcode == RISCV::TH_SDD); 0
3299 // The last operand of XTHeadMemPair instructions must be constant 3 or 4 ----
3300 // depending on the data width. ----
3301 if (IsTHeadMemPair32 && Inst.getOperand(4).getImm() != 3) { 0
3302 SMLoc Loc = Operands.back()->getStartLoc(); 0
3303 return Error(Loc, "Operand must be constant 3."); 0
3304 } else if (IsTHeadMemPair64 && Inst.getOperand(4).getImm() != 4) { 0
3305 SMLoc Loc = Operands.back()->getStartLoc(); 0
3306 return Error(Loc, "Operand must be constant 4."); 0
3307 } ----
3308 ----
3309 bool IsAMOCAS_D = Opcode == RISCV::AMOCAS_D || Opcode == RISCV::AMOCAS_D_AQ || 0
3310 Opcode == RISCV::AMOCAS_D_RL || 0
3311 Opcode == RISCV::AMOCAS_D_AQ_RL; ----
3312 bool IsAMOCAS_Q = Opcode == RISCV::AMOCAS_Q || Opcode == RISCV::AMOCAS_Q_AQ || 0
3313 Opcode == RISCV::AMOCAS_Q_RL || 0
3314 Opcode == RISCV::AMOCAS_Q_AQ_RL; ----
3315 if ((!isRV64() && IsAMOCAS_D) || IsAMOCAS_Q) { 0
3316 unsigned Rd = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3317 unsigned Rs2 = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
3318 assert(Rd >= RISCV::X0 && Rd <= RISCV::X31); 0
3319 if ((Rd - RISCV::X0) % 2 != 0) { 0
3320 SMLoc Loc = Operands[1]->getStartLoc(); 0
3321 return Error(Loc, "The destination register must be even."); 0
3322 } ----
3323 assert(Rs2 >= RISCV::X0 && Rs2 <= RISCV::X31); 0
3324 if ((Rs2 - RISCV::X0) % 2 != 0) { 0
3325 SMLoc Loc = Operands[2]->getStartLoc(); 0
3326 return Error(Loc, "The source register must be even."); 0
3327 } ----
3328 } ----
3329 ----
3330 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MII.get(Opcode); 0
3331 if (!(MCID.TSFlags & RISCVII::ConstraintMask)) 0
3332 return false; 0
3333 ----
3334 if (Opcode == RISCV::VC_V_XVW || Opcode == RISCV::VC_V_IVW || 0
3335 Opcode == RISCV::VC_V_FVW || Opcode == RISCV::VC_V_VVW) { 0
3336 // Operands Opcode, Dst, uimm, Dst, Rs2, Rs1 for VC_V_XVW. ----
3337 unsigned VCIXDst = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3338 SMLoc VCIXDstLoc = Operands[2]->getStartLoc(); 0
3339 if (MCID.TSFlags & RISCVII::VS1Constraint) { 0
3340 unsigned VCIXRs1 = Inst.getOperand(Inst.getNumOperands() - 1).getReg(); 0
3341 if (VCIXDst == VCIXRs1) 0
3342 return Error(VCIXDstLoc, "The destination vector register group cannot" 0
3343 " overlap the source vector register group."); 0
3344 } ----
3345 if (MCID.TSFlags & RISCVII::VS2Constraint) { 0
3346 unsigned VCIXRs2 = Inst.getOperand(Inst.getNumOperands() - 2).getReg(); 0
3347 if (VCIXDst == VCIXRs2) 0
3348 return Error(VCIXDstLoc, "The destination vector register group cannot" 0
3349 " overlap the source vector register group."); 0
3350 } ----
3351 return false; 0
3352 } ----
3353 ----
3354 unsigned DestReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
3355 // Operands[1] will be the first operand, DestReg. ----
3356 SMLoc Loc = Operands[1]->getStartLoc(); 0
3357 if (MCID.TSFlags & RISCVII::VS2Constraint) { 0
3358 unsigned CheckReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
3359 if (DestReg == CheckReg) 0
3360 return Error(Loc, "The destination vector register group cannot overlap" 0
3361 " the source vector register group."); 0
3362 } ----
3363 if ((MCID.TSFlags & RISCVII::VS1Constraint) && (Inst.getOperand(2).isReg())) { 0
3364 unsigned CheckReg = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
3365 if (DestReg == CheckReg) 0
3366 return Error(Loc, "The destination vector register group cannot overlap" 0
3367 " the source vector register group."); 0
3368 } ----
3369 if ((MCID.TSFlags & RISCVII::VMConstraint) && (DestReg == RISCV::V0)) { 0
3370 // vadc, vsbc are special cases. These instructions have no mask register. ----
3371 // The destination register could not be V0. ----
3372 if (Opcode == RISCV::VADC_VVM || Opcode == RISCV::VADC_VXM || 0
3373 Opcode == RISCV::VADC_VIM || Opcode == RISCV::VSBC_VVM || 0
3374 Opcode == RISCV::VSBC_VXM || Opcode == RISCV::VFMERGE_VFM || 0
3375 Opcode == RISCV::VMERGE_VIM || Opcode == RISCV::VMERGE_VVM || 0
3376 Opcode == RISCV::VMERGE_VXM) ----
3377 return Error(Loc, "The destination vector register group cannot be V0."); 0
3378 ----
3379 // Regardless masked or unmasked version, the number of operands is the ----
3380 // same. For example, "viota.m v0, v2" is "viota.m v0, v2, NoRegister" ----
3381 // actually. We need to check the last operand to ensure whether it is ----
3382 // masked or not. ----
3383 unsigned CheckReg = Inst.getOperand(Inst.getNumOperands() - 1).getReg(); 0
3384 assert((CheckReg == RISCV::V0 || CheckReg == RISCV::NoRegister) && 0
3385 "Unexpected register for mask operand"); ----
3386 ----
